claim.claim-text:
1. A method for manufacturing a bag for containing a gas, the bag including a front sheet, a back sheet, and including a valve having a front side and a back side, and defining a seal formed between the front sheet of the bag and the front side of the seal, and between the back side of the valve and the back sheet of the bag, the method comprising the steps of: 
providing a roll of valve material; 
providing a roll of back sheet material; 
providing a roll of front sheet material; 
providing a vacuum cylinder for transferring said valve material to said back sheet material; 
forming longitudinal seals in said valve material to form individual valve members; 
separating adjacent individual valve members; 
spacing said adjacent individual valve members apart; 
forming the seal between the back sheet material and the back side of the individual valve member; 
applying the front sheet material to the combination of the valve member and the back sheet material; 
forming a seal between the back sheet material and the front sheet material; and 
forming a seal between the front sheet material and the front side of the individual valve member; 
wherein said vacuum cylinder maintains constant contact with said back sheet material.

2. A method for manufacturing a bag for containing a gas, the bag including a front sheet, a back sheet, and including a valve having a front side and a back side, and defining a seal formed between the front sheet of the bag and the front side of the seal, and between the back side of the valve and the back sheet of the bag, the method comprising the steps of: 
providing at least one roll of valve material; 
providing at least one roll of back sheet material; 
providing at least one roll of front sheet material; 
providing a vacuum cylinder for transferring said valve material from said at least one roll of valve material to said back sheet material; 
forming seals in said valve material to form individual valve members; 
separating adjacent individual valve members; 
rotatably spacing said adjacent valve members apart from one another; 
forming the seal between the back sheet material and the back side of the individual valve member; 
applying the front sheet material to the combination of the valve member and the back sheet material; 
forming a seal between the back sheet material and the front sheet material; and 
forming a seal between the front sheet material and the front side of the individual valve member; 
wherein said vacuum cylinder maintains constant contact with said back sheet material.
